  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 3 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 6 high, 12 medium, 20 normal. Key bases needing attention include Larnaca (LCA/LCLK), M. R. Štefánik (BTS/LZIB) and Sofia (SOF/LBSF); plus 4 other bases. 12 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk, fog / freezing fog and mist  — most notably around David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Sofia (SOF/LBSF) and Tuzla (TZL/LQTZ). Network hotspots: Tenerife Sur (TFS/GCTS), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO). Primary drivers: low cloud base, thunderstorm / convective risk and snow / blowing snow. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Cologne Bonn (CGN/EDDK), Haugesund Airport, Karmøy (HAU/ENHD) and 9 others.",
